Contributor License Agreement (CLA)
Thank you for your interest in contributing to Locomotive!
By submitting code or other contributions to this project, you agree to the following terms and conditions:

1. Grant of Rights
By submitting contributions (including but not limited to code, documentation, and other materials) to Locomotive, you grant Locomotive's Team the irrevocable, worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free, and perpetual right to:

Use, reproduce, display, distribute, and modify the contributions.
Incorporate the contributions into the project and any derivative works of the project.
License or sublicense the contributions to third parties.
2. Ownership
You retain ownership of your contributions, but you acknowledge that once submitted, the contributions will be incorporated into the project and can be used in any way allowed by the project's license (which may be a proprietary license or an open-source license, as determined by the project owner).

3. No Copying, Modifying, or Redistributing the Entire Project
You understand that your contributions will be used as part of the project, but you cannot copy, modify, or redistribute the entire project without permission. This project is intended to be owned and controlled by dolovesvw, and contributions are subject to approval.

4. No Patent Claims
You agree not to assert any patent claims against Locomotive or its users for the use of your contributions.

5. No Warranty
The contributions are provided "as-is," without warranty of any kind, express or implied, including but not limited to the warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, or non-infringement.

6. Right to Reject
Locomotive reserves the right to accept or reject any contributions at its sole discretion.

How to Accept:
To indicate your acceptance of this Contributor License Agreement, simply submit a pull request with your contributions and acknowledge your understanding of these terms by including a statement like:
"I have read and agree to the Contributor License Agreement."
